  <title translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns the angle in degrees of the current segment of an object. &#160;The angle is measured in the counterclockwise direction relative to the grid with zero in the direction of positive </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="X_Prime" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">X_Prime</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;In the side view, zero is in the direction of positive </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Y" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Y</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. For SUTRA models, the angle is measured relative to the X-axis. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can range from +180 to -180.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can also be helpful in assigning </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Data_Sets_Required_by_SUTRA" anchor="ANGLE1" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">ANGLE1</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in SUTRA models. Both </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ObjectCurrentSegmentAngleDegrees</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Data_Sets_Required_by_SUTRA" anchor="ANGLE1" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">ANGLE1</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> are measured in a counterclockwise direction from the X-axis. </text></para>
  </body>
